Vice President Mike Pence attended the first-ever World Summit in Defense of Persecuted Christians on behalf of President Donald Trump. He reiterated the president's commitment to defending Christians and all those who suffer for their beliefs around the world. Pence acknowledged that Christians face significant hostility and hatred in over 100 countries, where they are subjected to intimidation, imprisonment, forced conversion, abuse, assault, and more. He highlighted the Middle East as an area where Christians are particularly targeted and emphasized that the Trump administration will provide relief and support to believers in need. Pence also emphasized that the US will continue to stand for religious freedom for all people, regardless of their faith.